asset.name: 1st Observer | 100 Limited Edition
asset.description:
The ongoing collection Observer was fisrt started late 2019 by the romanian artist Vladinsky as uniquely paintings made on cotton canvas. At the time this NFT was released the ongoing Observer Collection has a number of 576 paintings with more than 400 sold to collectors all over the world. At the same time a solo exhibition entitled Fragments of this ongoing Collection of Observer is running at the HOFA Lodnon Galerry in the heart of London and after that part of this exhibition will fly to Art Miami which was hosting the taped banana in 2019. 

The 100 Limited Edition is to celebrate the first ever made of the Observer ongoing Collection. The real painting will be exhibited along the last paintings of the Collection some time around the summer of 2022. The Observer Collection will have a number of 1.000 paintings but the challenge now is to keep it running as we are in the middle of creating one of the most well known series in the history of modern art.

asset.name: Pending Gerbil
asset.description:
The #PendingGerbil drew his breath nervously. Fail Dropped Dropped and Replaced There were nothing in this world he feared more.
He looked at the chords that crossed the abyss in front of him. They were loaded with pending gerbils, clinging for their life. No open space to be seen.
The world machine creaked under the load. As the wheel turned and settled on a new block with a load bang, the chords vibrated, and short shrieks were heard as tired paws lost their grip and the gerbils fell into oblivion.
#PendingGerbil closed his eyes, sent a short prayer to @VitalikButerin, and took the leap. Written by: @Werekitty1

Pending Gerbil is a very special collaboration with NonFunGerbils (https://nonfungerbils.com/pendinggerbil)

Design elements include a stack of blocks representing the blockchain technology bitcoin is based on, bitcoin genesis block code, a bear and bull to symbolize forces at play by market participants, the satoshi icon mask, & some discreet messages about bitcoin.

Although now effectively worthless, the Irony is that the 100 Trillion Zimbabwe note has value as a collector's item... a monumental example of why central banking and fiat currency make the world a worse place. asset.name: Resilience
asset.description:
Resilience, exposed in a futuristic exhibition.
Will human art withstand the challenge of time? Will our legacy survive nature? Will we be remembered?

The duality of Human art with its memory and its beauty versus the proof of time identified as nature, an immutable force, forever dancing together in a violent and wonderful dance.

In art, resilience is the capacity of the work of art to preserve through aesthetics its particularity distinguishing it from any other object, despite the increasing subjectivization in the production of works. Resilience in art appears as a response to the gradual setting aside of beauty during the twentieth century resulting today in an inability to define the work of art.
Psychological resilience is the ability to mentally or emotionally cope with a crisis or to return to pre-crisis status quickly. In simpler terms, it exists in people who develop psychological and behavioral capabilities that allow them to remain calm during crises/chaos and to move on from the incident without long-term negative consequences.

asset.name: The Magic Garden
asset.description: This was a magnificent, untamed garden- the plants that grew here were unlike any other with their reflective surfaces, swaying lively in the wind. This place was believed to have been enchanted many centuries ago, but those spells had long been lost. However, some theorize that this was a unique natural occurrence, caused by magic spilling out of the ground. Fortunately the garden was well protected from the outside, so it was likely to continue existing peacefully. This was a calm and safe place but the air felt a lot heavier here. The ground crackled beneath the hero's feet as she strolled along, filling the air with more chaotic magic. It was like a fountain of power, but at best it could only be guided by a skilled magician. However, the hero wasn't here in search of power, but rather she hoped to achieve a deeper reflection, looking to calm her growing inner turmoil. After a while, she noticed that the reflective mirrors were in fact distorting the reality, bending it with every movement, even showing things that weren't there. At first this made the hero uneasy, some distortions even showed her inner conflicts. Eventually she shifted her focus to the beauty all around her and the wonderful shimmering lights. She took in the new knowledge at a more comfortable slow pace, balancing the vague truths and her own comfort. Also the paths were unclear here, incredibly difficult to follow between all of the overgrown foliage. After many turns and squeezing through tight spaces, the hero finally stumbled upon a small clearing. As she stopped, she heard a new sound coming from one of the trees. She carefully approached a small creature, trying not to startle it. However, it appeared unperturbed and in fact delighted by her presence, hooting happily. This was the first live creature she encountered here, but she realized she wasn't fully paying attention before. At a second glace around her, with refreshed outlook, she noticed many eyes peering curiously back at her.

Photograph and Video by Hulki Okan Tabak. Limited Edition of 1. Minted November 11, 2020. Exclusively for KnownOrigin. Music by taskinjura from Pixabay and the piece is Mezhdunami - Uncut Gems.

Edwin McMasters Stanton was an American lawyer and politician who served as Secretary of War under the Lincoln Administration during most of the American Civil War. George Washington was an American political leader, military general, statesman, and Founding Father who served as the first president of the United States from 1789 to 1797. Previously, he led Patriot forces to victory in the nation's War for Independence. They appear on a United States stamp collection from 1870 and I have started to build this piece from actual used physical copies of those stamps.

With this video the USA 1870 series is concluded. Images are variations and derivations on the photographs from this session. The video is 15 seconds long with the intention to be looped. It's a soothing introspective outlook. A closure..

This is the 5th piece of a 5 artwork series that involves Edwin Stanton and George Washington from actual used 1870 stamps. The series consists of 4 digitally manipulated photographs and a video file. Various digital tools were used in creating the final images.

The matchboxes your family used to use, packets of candy, and typographic imperfections.
The old days are fun when we think about them.
And I mix myself and the stories that interest me go into it
to make art fresh
and this collection It's a collection that tells the story of my country.
Thailand and the contemporary twist
